enhanced_by.reason: The 'parents' method relies on the 'parent()' method to traverse up the parent hierarchy.
The 'parents' method checks if the parent's name is '#root' to determine the end of the parent chain.
Both 'parents' and 'children' methods return collections of elements, which can be used to construct assertions about the element's hierarchy.
The 'siblingElements' method returns a collection of sibling elements, which can be used to construct assertions about the element's position in the DOM.
